      <body>
         <entry xml:id="aqsios-dlgenr"
                xml:lang="en"
                type="mainEntry"
                prev="#aparsemon-dlgenr"
                next="#argentin-dlgenr"
                source="Genesis Rabbah">
            <form type="lemma" opt="false">
               <orth type="lemma" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false" select="true">אקסיוס</orth>
               <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">ʾqsyws</orth>
               <pron notation="rabbinic" opt="false">aqsios</pron>
               <gramGrp opt="false">
                  <gram type="pos" opt="false">adjective</gram>
               </gramGrp>
               <form type="variant" source="Vat1 Ox1 Ox2" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">אכסיוס</orth>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="K V" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">אכסיום</orth>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="Vat2" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">אכיוס</orth>
               </form>
            </form>
            <sense xml:id="aqsios-dlgenr-1" opt="false">
               <usg type="domain" opt="false"/>
               <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en" subtype="sense">
                  <quote>valued, estimable</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="translationEquivalent" xml:lang="grc">
                  <usg opt="false">
                     <lang opt="false">Classical Greek</lang>
                  </usg>
                  <quote>ἄξιος</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example" xml:lang="jpa">
                  <quote>תני מש' ר' אליעזר בן יעקב אני הוא שאין העולם ומלואו כדיי באלהותי, תרגם עקילס אקסיוס ואיקנוס</quote>
                  <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                     <ref type="witness">46,3</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">I 461: 2</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">איקנוס</ref>
                  <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                     <quote>It was taught in the name of R. Eliʿezer v. Yaʿaqov: It is I whose Godhead outweighs the world and the fullness thereof. Aquila translated it: worthy and adequate. (Cf. Freedman / Simon I 391)</quote>
                  </cit>
               </cit>
            </sense>
            <note anchored="true">
         See <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Jastrow I 113a</bibl>, <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">AC I 255ab</bibl>: from Gr. <term xml:lang="grc">ἰσκύον</term> (see there for other suggestions). <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Lеvy I 155b</bibl> renders for <term xml:lang="jpa">אקיוס</term>
               <term xml:lang="fjb">ʾqyws</term> (reading acc. to Arukh, and see AC ibid.; cf. Vat 2 <term xml:lang="jpa">אכיוס</term>
               <term xml:lang="fjb">ʾkyws</term>) Gr. <term xml:lang="grc">ἄκιος</term> fig. “everlasting”. Cf. <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">אקנוס</ref>
            </note>
            <ref type="bibliography">
               <bibl default="false" status="draft" facs="https://archive.org/details/GriechischeUndLateinischeLehnwrterInTalmudMidraschUndTargum/Griechische_und_lateinische_Lehnwrter2/page/n141/mode/2up">
                  <title>Krauss, LW II</title>
                  <citedRange>124a</citedRange>
               </bibl>
            </ref>
         </entry>
